### OhData TestBench — sample HTTP requests
### Use VS Code REST Client or JetBrains HTTP Client
### Start with: dotnet run --project src/OhData.TestBench.AspNetCore

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5099

# ── Service documents & metadata ─────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v2

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/$metadata

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/$metadata

###

# ── Products — collection queries ────────────────────────────────────────────

### All products
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products

###

### Filter by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$filter=Category eq 'Hardware'

###

### Filter by price range
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$filter=Price lt 15.00

###

### Order by price descending, take top 3
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$orderby=Price desc&$top=3

###

### Page: skip 2, take 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$skip=2&$top=2&$orderby=Id

###

### Inline count
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$count=true

###

### Inline count with filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$count=true&$filter=Category eq 'Electronics'

###

### Select specific properties
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$select=Name,Price

###

### Combine filter + orderby + select
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products?$filter=Price gt 10.00&$orderby=Price&$select=Name,Price,Category

###

### Count endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products/$count

###

### Count with filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products/$count?$filter=Category eq 'Hardware'

###

# ── Products — single item ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products(1)

###

### Get non-existent id → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products(999)

###

# ── Products — write operations ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a product
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "New Widget",
  "price": 7.50,
  "category": "Hardware"
}

###

### Update a product (replace)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products(1)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Widget",
  "price": 11.99,
  "category": "Hardware"
}

###

### Partial update
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products(1)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 8.99
}

###

### Delete a product
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products(3)

###

# ── Categories — simple GetAll (string key) ───────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Categories

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Categories('Hardware')

###

# ── Orders — navigation property routing (v2 only) ───────────────────────────

### All orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Orders

###

### Order by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Orders(11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111)

###

### Navigation route — order lines for a specific order
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Orders(11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111)/Lines

###

### Navigation route — different order
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Orders(22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222)/Lines

###

# ── ETags (if GetETag is configured) ─────────────────────────────────────────

### If-Match: optimistic concurrency check
### First get the ETag from a GET response, then use it:
PUT {{baseUrl}}/v1/Products(2)
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "some-etag-value"

{
  "name": "Updated Gadget",
  "price": 22.99,
  "category": "Electronics"
}

###

# ── Versioning — v2 has Orders, v1 does not ───────────────────────────────────

### Orders exist in v2
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Orders

###

### Orders do not exist in v1 → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Orders

###
